==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roseworm
<hw>Rose"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The larva of any one of several species of lepidopterous insects
which feed upon the leaves, buds, or blossoms of the rose, especially
<spn>Cacaecia rosaceana</spn>, which rolls up the leaves for a nest, and
devours both the leaves and buds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rosewort</ent>⟦br⟧
